SIMPLE: equalizer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Equalizer
<hw>E"qual*i`zer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, equalizes anything.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>same as <er>Equalizing bar</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A device, as a bar, for operating two brakes, esp. a
pair of hub brakes for an automobile, with equal force.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>Any device for equalizing the
pull of electromagnets; also, a conductor of low resistance joining the
armature ends of the series field coils of dynamos connected in
parallel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(A⟦eum⟧ronautics)</fld> <def>A sliding panel to
preserve the lateral stability of an a⟦eum⟧roplane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <fld>(Electronics)</fld> <def>a device or circuit within
a sound-reproducing system that reproduces the original frequency
distribution of the sound before recording by compensating for
inequalities in the frequency response of the system.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>a gun.</def> <mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equally</ent>⟦br⟧
